# Version placeholders: our version number and kei's have no 1:1
# correspondence, so unlike the rules above this needs BOTH sides mapped to
# the identical placeholder text (not one side mapped to the other's
# current value), or they'd still diff against each other every time either
# number changes.
Mihon [0-9]+\.[0-9]+(\.[0-9]+)?	PLACEHOLDER_APP_VERSION
Tsundoku [0-9]+\.[0-9]+(\.[0-9]+)?	PLACEHOLDER_APP_VERSION

# Same idea, for the ISSUE_TEMPLATE checklist item's bracket-link form
# (relies on the mihonapp/mihon rule above having already normalized the
# repo path on both sides).
\[[0-9]+\.[0-9]+(\.[0-9]+)?\]\(https://github\.com/tsundoku-otaku/tsundoku/releases/latest\)	[PLACEHOLDER_APP_VERSION](PLACEHOLDER_APP_LINK)
